&lt;p&gt;REGISTERED NURSE: BAND 6&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;BRAMBLE UNIT&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;DIRECTORATE OF CHILD AND WOMEN’S HEALTH&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ROYAL DEVON AND EXETER NHS FOUNDATION TRUST&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;REF: 185- A-20-91416 CLOSING DATE: 11/11/2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Would you value the opportunity of working in a progressive Children’s unit?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We require experienced paediatric nurses for Band 6 permanent posts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bramble Unit in Exeter has approx 45 beds providing care to children of all ages admitted to our acute inpatient unit, high dependency unit, attending our day care and outpatients services and also in our paediatric assessment unit. You will join a highly skilled and motivated nursing team and will be expected to work in any area of the trust where children are cared for.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hours: 37.5 hrs per week including weekends and internal rotation to night duty.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Salary: Band 6 - £31,365-£37,890 per annum (depending on skills &amp; experience)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information and/or to arrange an informal visit contact one of the unit Clinical Nurse Managers (01392) 402695/3092 or via switch board 01392 411611 bleep 603&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Safeguarding children is key to our business and this post has been identified as involving access to vulnerable children and /or adults and in line with Trust policy successful applicants will be required to undertake an enhanced disclosure check&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note if you are successful in obtaining an interview you will be notified via email. You will be given a minimum of 1 weeks notice, prior to your interview date. If you have not heard from us within 3 weeks of the closing date, please assume that your application has not been successful on this occasion.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our vision is to provide safe, high quality seamless services delivered with courtesy and respect. To achieve our vision we expect all our staff to uphold our Trust values. Our Trust values are: &lt;br /&gt; Honesty, Openness &amp; Integrity&lt;br /&gt; Fairness&lt;br /&gt; Inclusion &amp; Collaboration&lt;br /&gt; Respect &amp; Dignity&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;***Preference will be given to staff with ‘Priority’ and &#39;At Risk&#39; status including NHS At Risk staff throughout Devon.***&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;DUE TO THE ANTICIPATED HIGH NUMBER OF APPLICATIONS FOR THIS POST WE RESERVE THE RIGHT TO CLOSE THE VACANCY BEFORE THE CLOSING DATE.&lt;/p&gt;
